Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Diced British Chicken Breast{1%pack}, 5-6 mins. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 
> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Stir the @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Tomato Puree{30%g}, 
@Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{100%ml} into the chicken.

Bring to the boil, then simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}. 
> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Next, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @BBQ Sauce{48%g}, @Butter{20%g} and half the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}. 
Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share the rice out between your #bowls{}.

Spoon the chicken over the rice.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese and @Crispy Onions{1%sachet}.

Enjoy!